*----------------------------------------------------------------------
* test/fence_function/t10_error_handling.sno
* FENCE(P) with non-pattern argument should produce error 259
* ("fence argument is not pattern" — from SPITBOL).
* In CSNOBOL4 this becomes the standard "illegal data type" error.
*
* Also verify FENCE(P) where P is a string (should be auto-converted).
*----------------------------------------------------------------------

*   String argument: SNOBOL4 allows string-as-pattern (literal match)
               S = 'hello world'
               S  FENCE('hello') . w                               :F(FAIL10A)
               OUTPUT = IDENT(w, 'hello') 'PASS t10a: string arg to FENCE = [' w ']'
                                                                   :S(T10B)
               OUTPUT = 'FAIL t10a: expected hello got [' w ']'   :(END)
FAIL10A        OUTPUT = 'FAIL t10a: string arg match failed'       :(END)

*   Integer argument: should fail/error (not a valid pattern)
T10B           &ERRLIMIT = 1
               FENCE(42)                                           :S(FAIL10B)F(PASS10B)
FAIL10B        OUTPUT = 'FAIL t10b: FENCE(integer) should not succeed'  :(END)
PASS10B        OUTPUT = 'PASS t10b: FENCE(integer) failed as expected (bad arg)'
END
